<H2><U>
<a name="figures">Important Yaqui Mythological Figures</a>
</u></H2>

<B><img src="vinesmall.jpg"><font size=4><I><U>Itom Ae</font></U></B></I>:
Mother Earth in traditional Yaqui religion (her name literally means "our mother.") 
She was considered to be the mother and guardian of the 
Yaqui people. After Catholicism was adopted by the Yaquis, she became merged with Jesus' 
mother Mary (a situation that is common in Mexico, where pre-Columbian goddesses often 
became absorbed into local versions of Mary.) Today, most Yaquis 
consider the Virgin Mary and Itom Ae to be one and the same.

<H2><U>
Yaqui Indian Folklore
</u></H2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
http://www.sacred-texts.com/nam/sw/yml/index.htm
">Yaqui Myths and Legends</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Online collection of Yaqui legends and traditional stories.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
https://parentseyes.arizona.edu/node/506
">The Surems and the Talking Tree</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <B><A HREF="
http://www.sacred-texts.com/nam/sw/yml/yml06.htm
">Yomumuli and the Little Surem People</a>:</b> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Yaqui legend about a Surem woman who foretold the future.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
https://parentseyes.arizona.edu/node/512
">The Yaqui Curandero</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <B><A HREF="
http://www.sacred-texts.com/nam/sw/yml/yml62.htm
">The Yaqui Doctor</a>:</b> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Yaqui legends about a traditional healer punished for cheating death.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
https://parentseyes.arizona.edu/node/509
">The Enchanted Pascola</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Yaqui legend about a clumsy dancer who received powers from a magic goat.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
https://parentseyes.arizona.edu/node/510
">Ku Wikit</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <B><A HREF="
http://www.sacred-texts.com/nam/sw/yml/yml07.htm
">The Ku Bird</a>:</b> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Yaqui stories about the origin of the first parrot.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
https://parentseyes.arizona.edu/node/513
">How The Mountains Were Created</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
A Yaqui fusion legend about how Itom Ae and Jesus made the mountains.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
https://parentseyes.arizona.edu/node/519
">The Legend of Skeleton Mountain</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <B><A HREF="
http://www.sacred-texts.com/nam/sw/yml/yml26.htm
">The Big Bird</a>:</b> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Yaqui legends about a monster bird that carried off people.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
https://parentseyes.arizona.edu/node/511
">The Snake People</a>:</b> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Yaqui story about a man punished for injuring a snake.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
https://parentseyes.arizona.edu/node/520
">The Singing Tree</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Yaqui myth about a prophecy received from a sacred tree.

<H2><U>
<a name="books">Recommended Books on Yaqui Mythology</a>
</u><BR><font size=2>Our organization earns a commission from any book bought through these links</font>
</u></H2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0816504679/natilangofthe-20
">Yaqui Myths and Legends</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Collection of Yaqui legends and traditional stories.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1570670579/natilangofthe-20
">Deer Dance: Yaqui Legends of Life</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Another good collection of Yaqui myths and folklore.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0688148379/natilangofthe-20
">The Deetkatoo</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Great collection of traditional tales about little people from the Yaqui and other tribes. 
<BR>

